</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-style:italic;">$747 million</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-style:italic;">, or </font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-style:italic;">$1.14</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-style:italic;">&#32;per share</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">CHICAGO, Nov. 4, 2014 &#8211; Archer Daniels Midland Company (NYSE: ADM) today reported financial results for the quarter ended Sept.&#160;30, 2014.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">The company reported adjusted earnings per share</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;"><sup style="vertical-align:top;line-height:120%;font-size:pt">1</sup></font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">&#32;of </font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">$0.81</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">, up from </font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">$0.47</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">&#32;in the same period last year. Adjusted segment operating profit</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;"><sup style="vertical-align:top;line-height:120%;font-size:pt">1</sup></font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">&#32;was </font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">$914 million</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">, up </font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">45</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">&#32;percent from </font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">$632 million</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">&#32;in the year-ago period. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">Net earnings for the quarter were </font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;">$747 million</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">, or </font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;">$1.14</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">&#32;per share, and segment operating profit</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;"><sup style="vertical-align:top;line-height:120%;font-size:pt">1</sup></font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">&#32;was $1.07 billion.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">&#8220;The team delivered very strong results in the third quarter and made significant progress improving earnings and returns,&#8221; said ADM Chairman and CEO Patricia Woertz. &#8220;Corn Processing managed their product mix to serve good demand and optimize margins. Continued improvement in international merchandising results supported the ongoing recovery of Ag Services. And Oilseeds Processing again delivered solid results overall, benefiting from good demand and its diverse footprint and product portfolio.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">&#8220;We also continued to advance our portfolio management. Since the beginning of the third quarter, we signed a deal to sell our global chocolate business; we reached an agreement to acquire Specialty Commodities Incorporated; and we completed our acquisition of WILD Flavors. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">&#8220;In mid-October, we completed our previously announced buyback of 18 million shares, ahead of our year-end target. Given the strength of our balance sheet and our strong cash flows, we expect to repurchase up to 10 million more shares by the end of 2014.&#8221;</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;">Third</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;">&#32;Quarter </font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;">2014</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;">&#32;Highlights</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;"><sup style="vertical-align:top;line-height:120%;font-size:pt">1</sup>&#160;</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;padding-left:61px;text-indent:-24px;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;"><br></font></div><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="font-family:Times New Roman; a $156 million pretax gain on the expansion of the ADM-Marubeni joint venture; and a $102 million pretax loss on foreign exchange hedging of the WILD Flavors equity purchase. As a result of Euro depreciation, and net of these hedging losses, ADM&#8217;s purchase price of the WILD Flavors equity was $114 million below the price at signing.</font></div></td></tr></table><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:61px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:12pt;padding-left:37px;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">&#8226;</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">Agricultural Services increased </font><font style="font-family:Calibri;font-size:12pt;">$57 million</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">, with improvements in international merchandising and transportation.</font></div></td></tr></table><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:61px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:12pt;padding-left:37px;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">&#8226;</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">Trailing four-quarter-average adjusted ROIC was 8.5 percent, up 280 basis points year over year.</font></div></td></tr></table><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:61px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:12pt;padding-left:37px;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">&#8226;</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">The net debt position of the company declined to $0.7 billion, compared with $</font><font style="font-family:Calibri;font-size:12pt;">3.4 billion</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">&#32;at the end of the same period last year, which also resulted in a lower net interest expense.</font></div></td></tr></table><br><div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;text-indent:8px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:10pt;"><sup style="vertical-align:top;line-height:120%;font-size:pt">1</sup></font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:10pt;">&#32;Non-GAAP financial measures; see pages 4 and 9 for explanations and reconciliations, including after-tax amounts.</font></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><a name="s58580F13C83D54E55790CBB04BA5F1BC"></a><div></div><br><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;">Oilseeds Earnings Solid, with Lower South American Origination Offset by Improved Global Oilseed Processing, Biodiesel and Cocoa</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">Oilseeds operating profit of </font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">$366 million</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">&#32;was similar to the same period one year earlier.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">Crushing and origination operating profit declined </font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">$28 million</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">&#32;to </font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">$214 million</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">. Softseed results improved significantly, driven primarily by European rapeseed margins and volumes. Soybean crushing results rose as South American and European operations saw higher capacity utilization and better margins. However, continued slow farmer selling limited origination volumes and profits in South America.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">Refining, packaging, biodiesel and other generated a profit of </font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">$96 million</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">&#32;for the quarter, up </font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">$11 million</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">, with improved results from biodiesel in North America and Europe.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">Cocoa and other earned </font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">$30 million</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">&#32;in the quarter, up </font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">$20 million</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">&#32;from the year-ago period, reflecting the improved margin environment and higher capacity utilization in the cocoa business.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">&#160;</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">Oilseeds results in Asia for the quarter were down </font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">$3 million</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">&#32;from the same period last year, principally reflecting weaker results from Wilmar International Limited.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;">Corn Processing Results Improved Significantly on Strong Performances Across the Segment</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">Corn processing operating profit nearly doubled from $180 million to </font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">$356 million</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">Sweeteners and starches results increased </font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">$63 million</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">&#32;to </font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">$171 million</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">&#32;on steady volumes, with the expected lower average selling prices more than offset by the benefit of lower net corn costs.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">Bioproducts results increased </font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">$113 million</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">&#32;to </font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">$185 million</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">&#32;driven by solid ethanol demand and margins through most of the quarter. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;">Agricultural Services Results Improve on International Merchandising and Transportation</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">Agricultural Services operating profit was </font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">$159 million</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">, up </font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">$57 million</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">&#32;from the year-ago period. This excludes a gain of $156 million related to the expansion of the ADM-Marubeni joint venture, Pacificor, formerly the Kalama Export Company. Last year's result included approximately $30 million related to intercompany insurance settlements.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">Merchandising and handling earnings increased </font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">$60 million</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">&#32;to </font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">$64 million</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">, with significant improvements in international merchandising results more than offsetting the impact of the normal seasonal decline in U.S. export volumes until harvest began in September.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">Transportation results increased </font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">$14 million</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">&#32;to </font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">$35 million</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">, with higher barge freight volumes and rates.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">Milling and other results declined $17 million to $60 million on lower margins and volumes in the milling business.</font></div><br><div><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;">Page 2</font></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><a name="s58580F13C83D54E55790CBB04BA5F1BC"></a><div></div><br><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;">Other Items of Note</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">This quarter&#8217;s effective tax rate was </font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">28</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">&#32;percent, versus </font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">32</font><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">&#32;percent in the same period last year. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">ADM incurred a $102 million pretax loss on foreign exchange hedging of the WILD Flavors equity purchase.&#160;During the period from signing on July 5 to closing on Oct. 1, ADM progressively hedged the anticipated cash outflow related to the equity purchase.&#160;The Euro depreciated significantly, particularly in the month of September, resulting in losses on those hedges.&#160;As a result of the overall depreciation of the Euro, ADM's total purchase price of the equity, net of these hedging losses, was $114 million lower than on July 5, when the purchase agreement was signed.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">Included in Corporate results was a $56 million loss related to updated valuations of CIP&#8217;s portfolio of investments. ADM holds a 43.7 percent equity interest in CIP, a joint venture that targets investments in food, feed ingredients and bioproducts businesses.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">As additional information to help clarify underlying business performance, the tables on page 9 include both adjusted EPS as well as adjusted EPS excluding significant timing effects. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;">Conference Call Information</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">ADM will host a conference call and audio webcast on Nov. 4, 2014, at 8 a.m. Central Time to discuss financial results and provide a company update. A financial summary slide presentation will be available to download approximately 60 minutes prior to the call. To listen to the call via the Internet or to download the slide presentation, go to&#160;www.adm.com/webcast. To listen by telephone, dial (888) 522-5398 in the U.S. or (706) 902-2121 if calling from outside the U.S. The access code is 14811848.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">Replay of the call will be available from Nov. 5, 2014, to Nov. 11, 2014. The replay will also be available online for an extended period of time at www.adm.com/webcast.&#160;</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;">About ADM</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;">For more than a century, the people of Archer Daniels Midland Company (NYSE: ADM) have transformed crops into products that serve the vital needs of a growing world. Today, we&#8217;re one of the world&#8217;s largest agricultural processors and food ingredient providers, with more than 33,000 employees serving customers in more than 140 countries. With a global value chain that includes more than 470 crop procurement locations, 285 ingredient manufacturing facilities, 40 innovation centers and the world&#8217;s premier crop transportation network, we connect the harvest to the home, making products for food, animal feed, chemical and energy uses. Learn more at www.adm.com.&#160;</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:12pt;"><br></font></div><div style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif;font-size:10pt;">Segment operating profit is ADM&#8217;s consolidated income from operations before income tax excluding corporate items. Adjusted segment operating profit is segment operating profit adjusted, where applicable, for specified items and timing effects (see items denoted*). Timing effects relate to hedge ineffectiveness and mark-to-market hedge timing effects. Management believes that segment operating profit and adjusted segment operating profit are useful measures of ADM&#8217;s performance because they provide investors information about ADM&#8217;s business unit performance excluding corporate overhead costs as well as specified items and timing effects. Segment operating profit and adjusted segment operating profit are non-GAAP financial measures and are not intended to replace earnings before income tax, the most directly comparable GAAP financial measure. Segment operating profit and adjusted segment operating profit are not measures of consolidated operating results under U.S. GAAP and should not be considered alternatives to income before income taxes or any other measure of consolidated operating results under U.S. GAAP.</font></div><br><div style="text-align:center;"><div
